cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes a genetic algorithm for hyperparameter optimization of artificial neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of population-based training (PBT) and optimization of various types of neural networks, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the optimization of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), recurrent neural networks (RNNs), dense neural networks, and capsule networks, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
